01:26:43.000 --> 01:26:45.000
that in small companies

01:26:45.000 --> 01:26:47.000
there may not be separate services,

01:26:47.000 --> 01:26:49.000
departments, brigades and positions,

01:26:49.000 --> 01:26:51.000
but the function of the management account

01:26:51.000 --> 01:26:53.000
and management accountability.

01:26:53.000 --> 01:26:55.000
How much we spend, how much we earn.

01:26:55.000 --> 01:26:57.000
But in larger companies

01:26:57.000 --> 01:26:59.000
such a service usually appears.

01:26:59.000 --> 01:27:01.000
I want to tell you about it on this slide.

01:27:01.000 --> 01:27:03.000
So, when we have a larger company,

01:27:03.000 --> 01:27:05.000
in terms of size,

01:27:05.000 --> 01:27:07.000
we have a question

01:27:07.000 --> 01:27:09.000
who from the structural units

01:27:09.000 --> 01:27:11.000
to what extent to entrust this function,

01:27:11.000 --> 01:27:13.000
the function of the management account

01:27:13.000 --> 01:27:15.000
and management accountability.

01:27:15.000 --> 01:27:17.000
Very often it is entrusted to the financial director.

01:27:17.000 --> 01:27:19.000
He has a number of other questions

01:27:19.000 --> 01:27:21.000
in the management instruction.

01:27:21.000 --> 01:27:23.000
To manage the accounting,

01:27:23.000 --> 01:27:25.000
to build relations with the capital market,

01:27:25.000 --> 01:27:27.000
to manage the movement of money.

01:27:27.000 --> 01:27:29.000
But in addition to this,

01:27:29.000 --> 01:27:31.000
the function of the management account

01:27:31.000 --> 01:27:33.000
is often entrusted to the financial director.

01:27:33.000 --> 01:27:35.000
The second scheme on this slide

01:27:35.000 --> 01:27:37.000
differs from the first.

01:27:37.000 --> 01:27:39.000
It assumes that the function of the management account

01:27:39.000 --> 01:27:41.000
is cut out of the subordination of the financial director

01:27:41.000 --> 01:27:43.000
directly to the director.

01:27:43.000 --> 01:27:45.000
The director is the one

01:27:45.000 --> 01:27:47.000
who decides

01:27:47.000 --> 01:27:49.000
whether the financial director

01:27:49.000 --> 01:27:51.000
is subordinate to the director.

01:27:51.000 --> 01:27:53.000
This is how German companies

01:27:53.000 --> 01:27:55.000
often do it.

01:27:55.000 --> 01:27:57.000
Because they understand

01:27:57.000 --> 01:27:59.000
the function of the controlling

01:27:59.000 --> 01:28:01.000
as the function of an internal advisor.

01:28:01.000 --> 01:28:03.000
Maybe it will be appropriate

01:28:03.000 --> 01:28:05.000
to make an analogy

01:28:05.000 --> 01:28:07.000
with the novel

01:28:07.000 --> 01:28:09.000
The Godfather.

01:28:09.000 --> 01:28:11.000
If we imagine the organization

01:28:11.000 --> 01:28:13.000
of this novel,

01:28:13.000 --> 01:28:15.000
there was Don

01:28:15.000 --> 01:28:17.000
who led a number

01:28:17.000 --> 01:28:19.000
of structural units.

01:28:19.000 --> 01:28:21.000
But he was a person

01:28:21.000 --> 01:28:23.000
who could consult

01:28:23.000 --> 01:28:25.000
with Don

01:28:25.000 --> 01:28:27.000
as a staff body,

01:28:27.000 --> 01:28:29.000
as a consul,

01:28:29.000 --> 01:28:31.000
as an Italian advisor.

01:28:31.000 --> 01:28:33.000
The function of the consul

01:28:33.000 --> 01:28:35.000
is different.

01:28:35.000 --> 01:28:37.000
On the one hand,

01:28:37.000 --> 01:28:39.000
it is intended to ensure

01:28:39.000 --> 01:28:41.000
that all the canons

01:28:41.000 --> 01:28:43.000
that should be strictly observed

01:28:43.000 --> 01:28:45.000
are properly observed.

01:28:45.000 --> 01:28:47.000
In addition, this structure

01:28:47.000 --> 01:28:49.000
collects all the information

01:28:49.000 --> 01:28:51.000
and processes it

01:28:51.000 --> 01:28:53.000
and puts it on the management

01:28:53.000 --> 01:28:55.000
table along with the added value

01:28:55.000 --> 01:28:57.000
and advice.

01:28:57.000 --> 01:28:59.000
That is why some German companies

01:28:59.000 --> 01:29:01.000
like to make such a structure

01:29:01.000 --> 01:29:03.000
when the financial director

01:29:03.000 --> 01:29:05.000
deals with accounting issues,

01:29:05.000 --> 01:29:07.000
construction issues

01:29:07.000 --> 01:29:09.000
with the market fund

01:29:09.000 --> 01:29:11.000
and money management issues.

01:29:11.000 --> 01:29:13.000
The function of the controlling

01:29:13.000 --> 01:29:15.000
is in a separate unit.

01:29:15.000 --> 01:29:17.000
The same is true

01:29:17.000 --> 01:29:19.000
for the budget.

01:29:19.000 --> 01:29:21.000
If the sales department

01:29:21.000 --> 01:29:23.000
is going to Amsterdam,

01:29:23.000 --> 01:29:25.000
what can be the procedure

01:29:25.000 --> 01:29:27.000
for the approval of this business trip?

01:29:27.000 --> 01:29:29.000
It should come to the controlling department

01:29:29.000 --> 01:29:31.000
and check

01:29:31.000 --> 01:29:33.000
whether this business trip was in the budget.

01:29:33.000 --> 01:29:35.000
If it was not there,

01:29:35.000 --> 01:29:37.000
there is a chance that the sales department

01:29:37.000 --> 01:29:39.000
will not go.

01:29:39.000 --> 01:29:41.000
The remaining funds

01:29:41.000 --> 01:29:43.000
are enough to go to Amsterdam.

01:29:43.000 --> 01:29:45.000
For example, the sales department

01:29:45.000 --> 01:29:47.000
can take money from the adjacent

01:29:47.000 --> 01:29:49.000
advertising articles or from

01:29:49.000 --> 01:29:51.000
unforeseen expenses

01:29:51.000 --> 01:29:53.000
that can be up to 5% of the budget.

01:29:53.000 --> 01:29:55.000
It can also turn to the general

01:29:55.000 --> 01:29:57.000
corporate reserve fund.

01:29:57.000 --> 01:29:59.000
Anyway, this issue should be

01:29:59.000 --> 01:30:01.000
agreed with the controlling department.

01:30:01.000 --> 01:30:03.000
The controlling department monitors

01:30:03.000 --> 01:30:05.000
the budget and conducts a management

01:30:05.000 --> 01:30:07.000
account. By giving a waiver,

01:30:07.000 --> 01:30:09.000
the treasury employees

01:30:09.000 --> 01:30:11.000
can pay the travel

01:30:11.000 --> 01:30:13.000
to Amsterdam.

01:30:13.000 --> 01:30:15.000
This is how this procedure can be carried out.

01:30:15.000 --> 01:30:17.000
It is very reasonable

01:30:17.000 --> 01:30:19.000
to make this

01:30:19.000 --> 01:30:21.000
separate structure

01:30:21.000 --> 01:30:23.000
for the controlling

01:30:23.000 --> 01:30:25.000
directly to the subordinate

01:30:25.000 --> 01:30:27.000
management or shareholder.

01:30:27.000 --> 01:30:29.000
A small example.

01:30:29.000 --> 01:30:31.000
The company operates in the spare parts market.

01:30:31.000 --> 01:30:33.000
It is built

01:30:33.000 --> 01:30:35.000
according to the divisional principle.

01:30:35.000 --> 01:30:37.000
The managing company has

01:30:37.000 --> 01:30:39.000
three SBEs,

01:30:39.000 --> 01:30:41.000
the so-called strategic business units,

01:30:41.000 --> 01:30:43.000
which operate in different markets

01:30:43.000 --> 01:30:45.000
selling spare parts,

01:30:45.000 --> 01:30:47.000
both light and cargo.

01:30:47.000 --> 01:30:49.000
The SBEs are made up of branches.

01:30:49.000 --> 01:30:51.000
How was it decided

01:30:51.000 --> 01:30:53.000
to designate this function?

01:30:53.000 --> 01:30:55.000
We see that

01:30:55.000 --> 01:30:57.000
the managing company has a finance department,

01:30:57.000 --> 01:30:59.000
which includes

01:30:59.000 --> 01:31:01.000
the general accounting,

01:31:01.000 --> 01:31:03.000
the general contract group,

01:31:03.000 --> 01:31:05.000
